Name: 1080 Line
Description: 1080 lines look like a string of short yellow dots, sometimes connected to form a line, with a frequency around 1080 Hz

Name: Blip
Description: Blips are short glitches with usually a symmetric 'teardrop' shape

Name: Chirp
Description: Chirps are the characteristic shape created by gravitational waves from inspiraling compact objects, sweeping upwards in frequency over time

Name: Extremely Loud
Description: Extremely Loud are caused by a major disturbance in the detectors, and cover most of the image

Name: Koi Fish
Description: Koi Fish are similar to blip glitches, but resemble a fish with a head, fins, and thin tail

Name: Low Frequency Burst
Description: Low Frequency Bursts are short or long bursts of low frequency noise, usually lower than about 50 Hz

Name: Low Frequency Line
Description: Low Frequency Lines occur at very low frequencies, and do not vary in frequency over long durations

Name: None of the Above
Description: This category is for glitches that do not look like any of the other categories

Name: No Glitch
Description: If you do not see any glitch in the image , choose this option

Name: Power Line (60 Hz)
Description: Power Line are narrow in frequency around 60 Hz and its harmonics (multiples of 60 Hz - i.e. 120 Hz, 180 Hz) and last 0.2-0.5 seconds

Name: Repeating Blips
Description: Repeating Blips are blips that are observed to repeat, often 0.25 or 0.5 seconds after one another

Name: Scattered Light
Description: Scattered Light are low-frequency, long duration, humpy glitches that usually have several lines stacked on top of each other

Name: Scratchy
Description: Scratchy glitches are repeated, small glitches at mid and high frequencies

Name: Violin Mode Harmonic
Description: Violin modes are short glitches at 500 Hz and harmonics (multiples of 500 Hz - i.e. 1000 Hz, 1500 Hz)

Name: Whistle
Description: Whistles (a.k.a. Radio Frequency Beat Notes) have a characteristic 'W' or 'V' shape
